20:00.552 --> 20:02.302
Where the hell have you been?

20:02.385 --> 20:05.802
I need you to bring me a gun.
Pier 44, Red Hook.

20:05.886 --> 20:06.844
[hangs up]

20:06.927 --> 20:07.761
♪♪♪

20:07.844 --> 20:09.010
Jesus.

20:09.093 --> 20:12.636
♪♪♪

20:12.719 --> 20:15.636
♪ uneasy music ♪

20:15.719 --> 20:20.844
♪♪♪

20:42.968 --> 20:45.886
[easy listening music
over speakers]

20:45.968 --> 20:50.886
♪♪♪

20:50.968 --> 20:53.177
I'd say it takes
about 20 years off,

20:53.260 --> 20:56.260
if that's what you're going
for.

20:56.344 --> 20:59.135
Yeah.
Yeah, I'm an old fucker, huh?

20:59.218 --> 21:01.093
But I still got a right hand
like a fucking hammer.

21:01.177 --> 21:02.093
Boom.

21:03.719 --> 21:05.594
That happens
from down here, you know.

21:05.677 --> 21:07.344
That moves first,
and then you--[grunts]

21:07.427 --> 21:09.677
Very butch.

21:09.761 --> 21:13.260
♪♪♪

21:13.344 --> 21:15.093
Can I try on those glasses?

21:15.177 --> 21:16.302
Sure.

21:16.385 --> 21:17.594
Just wanna see, you know?

21:17.677 --> 21:20.344
♪♪♪

21:20.427 --> 21:22.719
Ooh, tasty.

21:22.802 --> 21:23.927
Tasty.

21:25.552 --> 21:28.510
How much, uh--

21:28.594 --> 21:30.302
how much
for the entire wardrobe?

21:30.385 --> 21:32.344
Y-your whole thing,
just as it--as it is.

21:32.427 --> 21:33.968
- This whole thing?
- Yeah.

21:34.052 --> 21:35.052
- $500?
- Nah.

21:35.135 --> 21:35.802
$800?

21:35.886 --> 21:37.552
How about $1,000

21:37.636 --> 21:39.177
and a date?

21:39.260 --> 21:41.052
I'm sorry, kid.

21:41.135 --> 21:42.636
I don't swing that way
no more.

21:42.719 --> 21:45.093
But you used to.

21:45.177 --> 21:48.344
When you're in a tight spot,
you get creative.

21:48.427 --> 21:50.344
But I never got fucked
in the ass,

21:50.427 --> 21:51.761
or vice versa.

21:51.844 --> 21:53.719
♪♪♪

21:53.802 --> 21:55.260
$1,500.

21:55.344 --> 21:58.385
♪♪♪

21:58.469 --> 22:00.385
Does that include the chain?

22:00.469 --> 22:01.968
Sure.

22:02.052 --> 22:03.469
Deal.

22:05.844 --> 22:06.469
[ship horn blares]

22:15.636 --> 22:17.427
Hey.

22:17.510 --> 22:18.968
Where's the gun?

22:24.677 --> 22:26.385
What's going on?

22:26.469 --> 22:29.218
They arrested me last night.
Kept me in Staten Island.

22:29.302 --> 22:31.594
- Why?
- They know everything.

22:33.052 --> 22:34.469
Want me to work for Feratti.

22:35.636 --> 22:37.344
All right,
so what do you want to do?

22:37.427 --> 22:39.010
I gotta go get Bridget.

22:39.093 --> 22:40.135
They're outside
her apartment.

22:40.218 --> 22:42.469
- You can't do that.
- Why not?

22:42.552 --> 22:44.052
Because they know who you are.

22:44.135 --> 22:45.510
So?

22:45.594 --> 22:46.427
So what, you're gonna
shoot 'em?

22:48.636 --> 22:50.510
Let me go.

22:51.636 --> 22:52.968
No.

22:53.052 --> 22:53.761
Ray, they don't know

22:53.844 --> 22:54.927
what I look like.

22:55.010 --> 22:56.135
[Lena] Come on.

22:56.218 --> 22:58.177
I'll be fast, I promise.

22:59.385 --> 23:00.844
All right.

23:03.135 --> 23:05.469
Take her to my place
and sit with her.

23:05.552 --> 23:07.344
[Ray] Lena.

23:07.427 --> 23:09.052
Thanks.

23:09.135 --> 23:10.719
Yeah.

23:16.677 --> 23:18.385
[cell phone rings]

23:22.344 --> 23:23.302
Yeah?

23:23.385 --> 23:25.093
[Emerson] Mr. Donovan.

23:25.177 --> 23:27.385
We need to talk
about your friend Mac.

23:27.469 --> 23:29.594
Who is this?

23:29.677 --> 23:32.552
♪ suspenseful music ♪

23:32.636 --> 23:37.552
♪♪♪

24:18.344 --> 24:20.260
Patrolman responding
to a possible explosion

24:20.344 --> 24:22.052
on the corner of Van Brunt
and King.

24:22.135 --> 24:23.761
♪♪♪

24:23.844 --> 24:25.719
Hi.
I-I think a car blew up

24:25.802 --> 24:27.427
over there.

24:27.510 --> 24:32.636
♪♪♪

24:43.844 --> 24:45.636
[knocking]

24:45.719 --> 24:50.677
♪♪♪

24:50.761 --> 24:52.302
Why do I get the feeling
you had

24:52.385 --> 24:54.344
something to do
with that explosion?

24:54.427 --> 24:57.093
Because I just blew up a car.
Where's your boyfriend?

24:57.177 --> 24:58.968
You want to explain
what the fuck is going on?

24:59.052 --> 25:01.093
Yeah.
Will you text him?

25:01.177 --> 25:03.636
Tell him not to come back here.
Put this on.

25:05.927 --> 25:07.344
Bridge, I know.
I'm sorry,

25:07.427 --> 25:09.218
but I just--I need you
to do this.

25:09.302 --> 25:10.968
[sighs]

25:11.052 --> 25:12.844
You know
it's fucking ridiculous, right?

25:12.968 --> 25:14.510
I do, yes.

25:14.594 --> 25:18.093
♪♪♪

25:18.177 --> 25:20.218
[sighs]

25:20.302 --> 25:22.844
[sirens wail in distance]

25:25.177 --> 25:27.010
[firetruck horns honking]

25:27.093 --> 25:31.968
♪♪♪

25:49.594 --> 25:51.344
[Emerson]
The famed Hollywood fixer.

25:53.218 --> 25:54.677
[Ray] What do you want?

25:54.761 --> 25:56.636
Your friend Mac?

25:56.719 --> 25:59.135
He's caught between a rock
and a hard place.

25:59.218 --> 26:02.135
So?
It's not my problem.

26:02.218 --> 26:04.260
No, but Michael Radulovic,

26:04.344 --> 26:07.135
Daniel Bianchi,
Judge R. Gregory Scholl,

26:07.218 --> 26:09.218
Mayor Ed Feratti--

26:09.302 --> 26:11.177
they are your problem.

26:11.260 --> 26:13.761
Mine and yours, Mr. Donovan.

26:13.844 --> 26:16.802
You see, this whole dance--
it's over a private prison

26:16.886 --> 26:19.552
built on 70 acres
of wasteland in Staten Island.

26:19.636 --> 26:24.010
Arthur Kill houses
roughly 4,000 inmates.

26:24.093 --> 26:26.093
You know how much those bodies
made Feratti

26:26.177 --> 26:28.719
in kickbacks last year?

26:28.802 --> 26:30.968
Four, five million, at least.

26:31.052 --> 26:32.802
Probably more.

26:32.886 --> 26:34.510
What's your point?

26:34.594 --> 26:37.427
I want Feratti as badly
as you do,

26:37.510 --> 26:40.135
but I can't get him
without my informant.

26:40.218 --> 26:42.093
What's that got to do
with me?

26:42.177 --> 26:43.594
I want you to do
what they asked you to do.

26:43.677 --> 26:46.677
Fire a shot
at Anita Novak.

26:46.761 --> 26:48.552
That way, you and your family
will be safe,

26:48.636 --> 26:51.427
and Mac will avoid
serious time in Attica.

26:51.510 --> 26:54.427
I do that,
Feratti wins the election.

26:54.510 --> 26:57.719
That may be the battle,
but not the war.

26:57.802 --> 26:59.427
I'll arrest him eventually,

26:59.510 --> 27:02.385
and Arthur Kill
will go for auction.

27:02.469 --> 27:04.385
Sam Winslow will be
a happy woman.

27:12.093 --> 27:15.135
You know, I was sitting
in O'Donoghue's

27:15.218 --> 27:16.802
long before Sergeant McGrath

27:16.886 --> 27:19.719
hauled you into the 132nd.

27:19.802 --> 27:21.802
Yeah, I saw that, Ray.

27:23.344 --> 27:26.010
Saw a few other things, too.

27:26.093 --> 27:28.427
Like what?

27:28.510 --> 27:30.344
Fetu Autufuga
ring a bell?

27:30.427 --> 27:33.344
♪ melancholy music ♪

27:33.427 --> 27:36.135
I'd appreciate your help,

27:36.218 --> 27:38.260
in exchange for mine.

27:38.344 --> 27:41.260
♪ eerie ringing music ♪

27:41.344 --> 27:46.469
♪♪♪

27:47.552 --> 27:49.093
[helicopter blades chopping]

27:59.427 --> 28:00.677
[Mac] Yeah?

28:00.761 --> 28:02.218
Meet me at Stuyvesant Square.

28:02.302 --> 28:03.594
[phone beeps]

28:05.093 --> 28:07.135
♪♪♪

28:07.218 --> 28:08.677
Where the hell
have you been?

28:08.761 --> 28:10.552
Out looking for a job.

28:10.636 --> 28:11.761
[Bridget] You need to leave

28:11.844 --> 28:13.218
- the apartment.
- Huh?

28:13.302 --> 28:14.302
[Bridget] I'll explain later.

28:14.385 --> 28:15.260
Just, you need to leave.

28:15.344 --> 28:16.052
[knocking]

28:16.135 --> 28:17.344
Oh, hold on.

28:17.427 --> 28:18.594
There's somebody
at the door.

28:18.677 --> 28:20.636
- Who?
- [Smitty] I don't know.

28:20.719 --> 28:22.552
- I should answer it.
- [knocking]

28:22.636 --> 28:23.927
- It's probably, like, a--
- [Bridget] No, don't!

28:24.010 --> 28:25.218
No, could be, like, a cop,
or a firefighter.

28:25.302 --> 28:26.469
[Bridget] No, Smitty--

28:30.302 --> 28:31.218
Uh, yeah?

28:31.302 --> 28:32.719
I'm looking for Bridget.

28:32.802 --> 28:34.052
- Who is it?
- [Smitty] I don't know,

28:34.135 --> 28:35.052
it's some old dude.

28:35.135 --> 28:35.968
Looks like the guy

28:36.052 --> 28:36.927
from Boogie Nights.

28:37.010 --> 28:38.093
[Bridget] Mark Wahlberg?

28:38.177 --> 28:39.510
No, uh, you know,

28:39.594 --> 28:41.093
the Burt Reynolds guy,

28:41.177 --> 28:42.510
except he's a little taller.

28:42.594 --> 28:44.177
Hey.

28:44.260 --> 28:45.427
W-what do you want?

28:45.510 --> 28:47.719
I'm Bridget's grandfather.

28:47.802 --> 28:48.927
Oh, shit.

28:49.010 --> 28:49.844
What?

28:49.927 --> 28:51.260
It's your grandfather.

28:51.344 --> 28:52.886
What the fuck?

28:52.968 --> 28:54.844
Why is Mickey there?

28:54.927 --> 28:56.677
Is that her?

28:56.761 --> 28:57.844
Let me speak to her.

28:57.927 --> 28:59.927
He wants to talk to you.

29:00.010 --> 29:01.968
[Bridget] No, Smitty,
he is a fucking fugitive.

29:02.052 --> 29:04.802
She says that now is--
is not really a good time.

29:04.886 --> 29:05.886
Give me the phone, son.

29:09.552 --> 29:11.260
Good boy.

29:11.344 --> 29:12.552
Hey, sweet pea.

29:12.636 --> 29:13.719
[Mickey] How you doing?

29:13.802 --> 29:15.093
What do you want?

29:15.177 --> 29:16.719
I'm gonna be leaving, Bridge.

29:16.802 --> 29:18.886
I don't know when, if ever,
I'm

29:18.968 --> 29:21.218
gonna see you again.

29:21.302 --> 29:22.802
Put Smitty back on the phone.

29:22.927 --> 29:25.594
I just want you to know
I love you.

29:25.677 --> 29:28.093
[Bridget] Put him back
on the phone.

29:29.469 --> 29:30.385
Here.

29:33.218 --> 29:34.552
Hey.

29:34.636 --> 29:35.636
Hey.
Get him out of there,

29:35.719 --> 29:37.010
go to a coffee shop,

29:37.093 --> 29:38.302
and call me when you get there.

29:38.385 --> 29:39.927
All right.

29:43.093 --> 29:44.968
Hey, I gotta go.
Uh--

29:45.052 --> 29:46.302
You her boyfriend?

29:46.385 --> 29:48.844
I'm her fiancé.

29:48.927 --> 29:50.218
Wow.

29:53.218 --> 29:55.302
Congratulations.

29:55.385 --> 29:56.761
Yeah, thanks.

30:00.385 --> 30:02.802
Tell her I'm sorry
I wasn't a better grandfather.

30:02.886 --> 30:05.802
♪ desolate music ♪

30:05.886 --> 30:10.802
♪♪♪

30:13.552 --> 30:15.218
[door closes]

30:15.302 --> 30:20.135
♪♪♪

30:34.135 --> 30:36.052
How long you been wearing
a wire?

30:42.302 --> 30:44.594
Had a little talk with Emerson
on the piers today.

30:44.677 --> 30:47.677
I didn't know
who to turn to, Ray.

30:49.761 --> 30:52.177
I didn't know who to trust.

30:52.260 --> 30:55.344
I need you to believe me.
I wanted to tell you.

30:55.427 --> 30:57.802
A hundred fucking times,
I wanted to tell you.

30:57.886 --> 30:59.927
I just was so fucking spun.

31:01.594 --> 31:03.510
There's a guy named Will Evans

31:03.594 --> 31:05.594
paroled out of Rikers
yesterday.

31:05.677 --> 31:08.052
330 Water Street.

31:08.135 --> 31:11.302
I want you to pick him up
and hold him for possession.

31:11.385 --> 31:14.093
Why?

31:14.177 --> 31:16.469
You want me to take down
Anita Novak

31:16.552 --> 31:18.052
- or not?
- Yeah.

31:18.135 --> 31:20.886
Thank you, Ray.

31:20.968 --> 31:24.260
You know what happens
to cops in Attica, Ray?

31:24.344 --> 31:26.802
What would happen
to Jimmy and Amber?

31:26.886 --> 31:28.761
I did what I had to do, Ray.

31:28.844 --> 31:31.218
I did it for my family.

31:31.302 --> 31:34.218
Christ, you think I wanted
to put you in this position?

31:36.761 --> 31:39.469
Well, you did.

31:39.552 --> 31:40.802
Ray.

31:46.886 --> 31:49.552
[mournful country music
playing on speakers]

31:49.636 --> 31:52.135
♪♪♪

31:52.218 --> 31:53.719
[sighs]

31:56.010 --> 31:57.302
[man] On my way.

31:59.093 --> 32:03.968
♪♪♪

32:06.260 --> 32:07.469
Here you go.

32:42.968 --> 32:44.761
[bells jingle]

32:50.093 --> 32:51.927
[Daryll] Oh, shit.

32:52.010 --> 32:53.636
Okay, Bunch man,
where to first?

32:53.719 --> 32:55.552
Yo, how about we go to Fenway,

32:55.636 --> 32:57.677
go check out the Green Monster?

32:57.761 --> 32:59.968
Dodgers fans don't get
to go to Fenway.

33:00.052 --> 33:01.218
So what you saying?

33:01.302 --> 33:02.968
Saying that hat's fucking ugly.

33:03.052 --> 33:05.636
I thought it was the Yankees
you guys hated.

33:05.719 --> 33:07.802
It's Boston.
It's the Sox or nothing.

33:07.886 --> 33:08.802
Yeah, well,

33:08.886 --> 33:10.344
I'm a Dodger fan, man.

33:10.427 --> 33:11.469
I ain't take my hat off
for nobody.

33:11.552 --> 33:13.968
Yeah?
Your funeral.

33:14.052 --> 33:16.552
But seriously,
where are we going?

33:16.636 --> 33:18.802
See Ma and Bridge.

33:58.802 --> 34:00.844
Terry,

34:00.927 --> 34:03.802
is he gonna be all right?

34:03.886 --> 34:05.844
He wants to turn himself in.

34:05.927 --> 34:07.469
What?

34:07.552 --> 34:10.052
He can't see it any other way.

34:10.135 --> 34:12.427
I mean, that's freaking crazy,
Terry.

34:12.510 --> 34:15.761
So--I don't know.
What are we gonna do?

34:15.844 --> 34:18.052
Been trying
to figure that out, D.

34:38.344 --> 34:40.052
What do I say?

34:41.594 --> 34:43.052
I don't know.

34:44.802 --> 34:46.886
Hey, Ma.
Hey, Bridge.

34:55.344 --> 34:58.260
You know, I always think
about the fingernails.

35:00.135 --> 35:02.135
What?

35:02.218 --> 35:03.927
They keep on growing
after you die.

35:04.010 --> 35:06.719
You hear that?

35:06.802 --> 35:07.927
The toenails, too.

35:11.886 --> 35:14.844
You know, Ma was always
there for you,

35:14.927 --> 35:17.093
and she did the best she could.

35:20.385 --> 35:22.927
Now can we go
and get a drink?

35:24.218 --> 35:27.093
Kelly's?

35:27.177 --> 35:28.927
Sure.

35:37.260 --> 35:38.968
I miss you, Ma.

35:41.218 --> 35:42.761
I love you.

35:44.886 --> 35:46.385
I love you, Bridge.

35:48.844 --> 35:51.469
♪ desolate music ♪

35:51.552 --> 35:56.719
♪♪♪

36:07.093 --> 36:08.469
[knocking]

36:11.886 --> 36:13.135
Oh, shit.

36:13.802 --> 36:16.552
Come on in.

36:16.636 --> 36:18.260
Look, Ray.

36:18.344 --> 36:20.677
I don't know what you're up to,
but I didn't--

36:22.469 --> 36:23.761
[Ray] This is Robbi.
She's the executive producer

36:23.844 --> 36:25.302
of Nightly Nation.

36:25.385 --> 36:28.260
Nice to meet you, Justine.

36:28.344 --> 36:31.260
What the fuck is going on?

36:31.344 --> 36:33.010
Can you give us a minute?

36:42.177 --> 36:43.594
Sit down.

36:50.510 --> 36:51.927
[sighs]

36:56.052 --> 36:59.010
You're gonna be the lead guest
on Robbi's show.

36:59.093 --> 37:00.010
I want you to tell Billy Till

37:00.093 --> 37:01.802
that a man you never met before

37:01.927 --> 37:04.177
hired you to stage
the Central Park attack.

37:04.260 --> 37:07.344
You're gonna tell him
it was a fake.

37:07.427 --> 37:09.886
Why the fuck would I do that?

37:09.968 --> 37:12.010
Because your brother
just got arrested again.

37:12.093 --> 37:12.802
[Justine] What?
No, I--

37:12.886 --> 37:13.844
I was just with Will

37:13.927 --> 37:14.677
this morning.
He--

37:14.761 --> 37:16.385
I can get him out.

37:19.135 --> 37:20.469
You had my brother arrested.

37:23.427 --> 37:25.177
Does Lena know about this?

37:25.260 --> 37:27.677
Don't mention Lena's name,
or mine.

37:27.761 --> 37:29.135
Are we clear?

37:31.719 --> 37:33.927
You're a fucking asshole.

37:34.010 --> 37:35.218
Good.

37:39.927 --> 37:41.636
I don't see my kid, neither.

37:41.719 --> 37:43.135
Yeah?

37:43.218 --> 37:45.886
Fucking heartache of my life.

37:45.968 --> 37:46.844
[rock music over speakers]

37:46.927 --> 37:48.594
What happened?

37:50.218 --> 37:53.636
Screwed this barfly, Pamela,
in my marital bed.

37:53.719 --> 37:55.802
Stupid me.
[laughs]

37:55.886 --> 37:58.719
Wife came home,
caught us 69ing.

37:58.802 --> 38:00.385
That was before the accident.

38:01.886 --> 38:04.802
Next day, she took the kids
to her mother's in Allentown,

38:04.886 --> 38:07.469
never came back.

38:07.552 --> 38:09.802
If I could do it over,

38:09.886 --> 38:11.385
you know what I should've done?

38:11.469 --> 38:13.260
♪♪♪

38:13.344 --> 38:15.510
Taken Pamela
to a Motel 6.

38:15.594 --> 38:18.761
[laughs]

38:18.844 --> 38:21.302
♪♪♪

38:21.385 --> 38:22.927
Yeah, you oughta tell
your brother

38:23.010 --> 38:25.010
to take off that hat.

38:25.093 --> 38:26.761
I already fucking told him.

38:26.844 --> 38:28.052
So where's he been?

38:28.135 --> 38:30.677
Fuck if I know.

38:30.761 --> 38:33.093
Well, how you stay
with a guy like that?

38:33.177 --> 38:35.927
Well, first off,

38:36.010 --> 38:38.344
he's the father of my kid.

38:38.427 --> 38:42.427
Second off, uh, he loves me.

38:42.510 --> 38:44.010
♪♪♪

38:44.093 --> 38:46.552
Yeah, but do you love him?

38:46.636 --> 38:48.135
Enough.

38:48.218 --> 38:49.968
♪♪♪

38:50.052 --> 38:51.677
And what would Abby say?

38:51.761 --> 38:53.177
[laughs]

38:53.260 --> 38:55.260
Abby was a good aunt,

38:55.344 --> 38:57.093
She would just've given me

38:57.177 --> 38:59.177
a box of really fucking nice
hand-me-downs,

38:59.260 --> 39:02.927
tell me to keep a bank account
that Mike knows nothing about.

39:03.010 --> 39:04.968
Yeah, that's Abby.

39:05.052 --> 39:08.636
♪♪♪

39:08.719 --> 39:10.510
Let me get you another shot.

39:13.427 --> 39:17.802
♪♪♪

39:17.886 --> 39:19.802
[Billy] Now, folks,
just when you thought

39:19.886 --> 39:22.427
that politics couldn't get
